message.content:
cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper discusses various types of finite-state automata and their properties. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper includes an original algorithm for the intersection of one-way nondeterministic finite-state automata. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the decidability properties of the automata classes. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the closure properties of the automata classes. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the expressiveness of the automata classes.
